               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>
                           <material>Indian paper (?). Chickpea paper, well-burnished. Hand of main
                              text seems to be the same as earlier parts of codex.</material>
                        </support>
                        <extent>456 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="cm">
                              <height/>
                              <width/>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="cm">
                              <height/>
                              <width/>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation><p>Foliated with Roman numerals throughout. Persian numerals in
                              red only in the main text, starting on <locus>f.32</locus>. The final
                              folio <locus>f.456</locus> is also marked in red.</p></foliation>
                        <collation> </collation>
                        <condition>First few folios and some later have been repaired. Moderate worm
                           damage and staining.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout n="1" columns="1" ruledLines="0">
                           <p>Prefaces are not ruled or illuminated. Main text is ruled in sparkling
                              gold with lapis.Red rubrications.Folios <locus>30v-32r</locus>
                              blank.</p>
                           <dimensions type="line-height" unit="mm"/>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote scope="major" script="nasta_liq" medium="black"> Beautiful Indian
                        nastaʿlīq. Qur’anic verses in naskh.Scribe: <persName
                           xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="" role="scr">Saʿd Allāh Ibrāhīm
                           Ābādī</persName>.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="other"> Illuminated heading (sarlauh) at start of main text
                           <locus from="32v" to="32v">f.32v</locus></decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions><list>
                        <item><label>Marginalia: </label>Comments throughout, mostly marked لط –
                           presumably for ʿAbd al-Laṭīf</item>
                     </list>
                     <!-- <note>A high quality manuscript in terms of production, textual content and
                        provenance.</note>This is not a valid addition!!-->
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <p>Dark red leather. Doublures: reddish plain leather with silver
                           rulings.<dimensions unit="cm">
                           <height>25.8</height>
                           <width>14.3</width>
                           <depth >4.5</depth>
                        </dimensions>.</p>
                     <condition/>
                     <decoNote>Pressure moulded designs. Rectangular frame containing floral
                        designs; central turanj with 2 pendants above and 2 below, and corner
                        pieces, all decorated with flowers. Iinner pendants contain inscriptions:
                        عاقبت بخير باد; upper and lower boards identical.</decoNote>
                  </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
